.\" pktamp.8 - manual page for pktamp
.\"
.TH PKTAMP 8 "January 2026" "Version 1.0" "System Administration"

.SH NAME
pktamp \- Packet Capture Replay Web Interface

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pktamp
is a web-based interface for replaying packet capture files using tcpreplay.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Pktamp provides a Winamp-styled web interface that allows users to:
.IP \(bu 4
Upload packet capture files
.IP \(bu 4
Manage stored packet captures (rename, delete)
.IP \(bu 4
Select network interfaces for replay (including loopback)
.IP \(bu 4
Adjust replay speed from 0 (unlimited) to 10 Gbps
.IP \(bu 4
Start and stop packet replay
.IP \(bu 4
Replay multiple packet captures simultaneously

.SH INSTALLATION
See INSTALL.md for detailed installation instructions.

Briefly:
.IP 1. 4
Download and run the installer: ./install.sh
.IP 2. 4
Access the web interface at http://<bind_ip>:8080
.IP 3. 4
Click "Upload" to add packet capture files
.IP 4. 4
Select files, interface, and speed, then click "START"

.SH WEB INTERFACE
The web interface is accessible at http://<bind_ip>:8080

.SH COMMAND LINE USAGE
.PP
The service runs automatically after installation:
.BR systemctl start pktamp
.PP
To restart the service:
.BR systemctl restart pktamp
.PP
To view logs:
.BR journalctl -u pktamp -f

.SH API ENDPOINTS
.TP
.B GET /api/ping
Health check endpoint.
.TP
.B GET /api/interfaces
List available network interfaces.
.TP
.B GET /api/pcaps
List stored packet captures.
.TP
.B POST /api/pcaps
Upload a packet capture file.
.TP
.B PUT /api/pcaps/<name>
Rename a packet capture.
.TP
.B DELETE /api/pcaps/<name>
Delete a packet capture.
.TP
.B POST /api/replay
Start replaying selected packet captures.
.TP
.B DELETE /api/replay/<id>
Stop a replay.
.TP
.B GET /api/replay/<id>/status
Get status of a replay.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /opt/pktamp
Application directory
.TP
.B /var/lib/pktamp/pcaps
Directory for storing packet capture files
.TP
.B /etc/systemd/system/pktamp.service
Systemd unit file

.SH USER
The service runs as user
.B pktamp
with no login shell.

.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Linux
Debian/Ubuntu or RHEL/CentOS/AlmaLinux
.TP
.B Python 3.11+
.TP
.B tcpreplay
.TP
.B Root/sudo access
for installation

.SH SECURITY NOTES
.TP
.B capabilities
tcpreplay is granted CAP_NET_RAW and CAP_NET_ADMIN to run without root privileges.
.TP
.B Firewall
Port 8080 must be open for web interface access.

.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
.B Service won't start
Check logs: journalctl -u pktamp -n 50
.TP
.B Cannot access web UI
Verify firewall allows port 8080 and service is running.
.TP
.B Permission denied on tcpreplay
Run: sudo setcap cap_net_raw,cap_net_admin+eip $(which tcpreplay)

